Distribution. Through most of northern and central Europe, including Britain and Ireland (
Taeger et al . 2006
), south to the Iberian Peninsula ( Liston 2016 ), and Transpalaearctic ( Zhelochovtsev & Zinovjev 1995 ) through Russia ( Zhelochovtsev & Zinovjev 1995 ) to Hokkaido , Japan ( Togashi 1990 ) and Hubei Province , China ( Wei & Nie 1998 ). Occurrence in Sweden : published records; distributed throughout the whole of Scandinavia ( Thomson 1871 , as
Nematus degeeri
). Material examined: Skåne , Halland , Småland, Öland, Gotland , Östergötland , Västergötland, Bohuslän, Södermanland , Uppland, Västmanland , Dalarna , Gästrikland, Härjedalen, Jämtland , Ångermanland, Hälsingland, Norrbotten , Lycksele Lappmark, Lule Lappmark, Torne Lappmark.
